2021-09-22T20:37:09.560Z","cooked":"<p>Yes, many of the principles are very similar.  You should probably work closely with your mentor so that you both have the same expectations/plan, but here’s a bit more…</p>
<p>In general, different hardware says “Subsystem” to me, rather than different “RobotContainer”.  Do all of your robot containers have the same set of methods – do they all implement a common interface?  Of course, this is all based on the command-based programming model.  Since you used these terms, I suspect you and/or your mentor are leaning this way?  If so, consider using Command as your common interface.</p>
<p>It’s important to start out with a good approach, but sometimes jumping in and iterating can work well also.  Once you’ve got something working, make sure you really understand it well and then think about how you might restructure/refactor things to improve.  Think of the stuff in WPILib as good advice that can help you arrive at a good approach more quickly, by starting out from somewhere that has been mapped out by others who have accumulated this kind of wisdom.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2021-09-22T20:37:09.560Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":61,"readers_count":60,"score":17.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":396111,"topic_slug":"sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer","display_username":"Allen Nuttle","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49423,"username":"Gandagorn","name":"Elliot Scher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":14283,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer/396111/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2968979,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png","created_at":"2021-09-22T21:48:46.684Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks so much for the help!!!</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2021-09-22T21:48:46.684Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":57,"readers_count":56,"score":31.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":396111,"topic_slug":"sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer/396111/6","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2968988,"name":"Joe Ross","username":"Joe_Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png","created_at":"2021-09-22T23:09:26.614Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Gandagorn" data-post="1" data-topic="396111">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/48/267112_2.png" class="avatar"> Gandagorn:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>The way our code is written, we have multiple robotcontainers that house different commands and subsystems for whatever role we play in that match.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>I think it would be helpful to expand on this, to help determine the best solution. What changes physically on the robot for what role you play in the match. What changes in your controls based on what role you play in the match? What’s the consequence if you aren’t able to make a selection before the match, and you have to run whatever the default is?</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2021-09-22T23:09:26.614Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":49,"readers_count":48,"score":34.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":396111,"topic_slug":"sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer","display_username":"Joe Ross","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":65,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer/396111/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2968995,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png","created_at":"2021-09-23T01:04:46.420Z","cooked":"<p>It’s mostly just for ease of use during testing but if we’re pressed for time before a match and we decide we need to do something with a different robot container, we don’t want to have to re-deploy in the queue with a different robot container. For example, we want to be able to switch between a robot container that uses PID control to one that doesn’t if an encoder fails or something without having to redeploy if that makes sense. It’s mostly just to make it more user friendly and easy for our new drivers to understand.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2021-09-23T01:04:46.420Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":19.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":396111,"topic_slug":"sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":65,"username":"Joe_Ross","name":"Joe Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer/396111/8","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2968997,"name":"Allen Nuttle","username":"nuttle","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nuttle/{size}/124105_2.png","created_at":"2021-09-23T01:21:38.643Z","cooked":"<p>Not sure this is an exact fit for your use case, but using <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/vscode-overview/using-test-mode.html">test mode</a> is highly recommended for things you might do in the pit or generally testing and troubleshooting things.</p>
<p>Ultimately, you are adding user controls to change the behavior of your code, and this adds complexity – another possible failure point if things are not well tested with various combinations of these settings.  Test mode can at least isolate a lot of this complexity to a mode the robot will not see during a normal match.  Being able to switch out the entire container is sort of like being able to very quickly redeploy on the fly, so I can see the attraction.  But, it will be pretty important to structure your code cleanly so you can maintain it.  Going the other direction, you would push these controls down into various subsystems and just have a single RobotContainer.</p>
<p>If you have a unique RobotContainer for every combination of settings you want to control, that could turn into a large number pretty quickly.  Having multiple controls is an option that might make more sense in some cases, but it all really depends – there could be downsides here too.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2021-09-23T01:21:38.643Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":18.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":396111,"topic_slug":"sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer","display_username":"Allen Nuttle","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/vscode-overview/using-test-mode.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Using Test Mode — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49423,"username":"Gandagorn","name":"Elliot Scher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":14283,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/sendablechooser-for-choosing-specific-robotcontainer/396111/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2969035,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chi